Class Link

  • java.lang.Object
    • Link
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, Locatable

    public class Link
extends java.lang.Object
implements Locatable, java.io.Serializable
    This class represents a pointer to an Individual. It is used to allow the User to place a pointer to someone on Chart A when that Individual's "home chart" is not A. For example: Sammy is a child of the Smith family of Chart B. Sally is a child of the Forth family of Chart D. When Sammy marries Sally, we decide which chart will contain the marriage (assume B here). The Union symbol is added to chart B and Sammy is made a spouse in it. Then a Link to Sally is added to Chart B and also made a spouse in the Union. Over on Chart D, Sally's Detail Display shows that her Home Chart is D, and has a drop-down menu of all her links. On Chart B, the Link symbol for Sally is green to show it is a Link. Her Detail Display is the same as on D, showing her Home Chart and the menu of all her links.
